  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1">Auto-Layer</para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Heading3_atocs_" style="page-break-before:always;">What is &apos;Auto-Layer&apos;?</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="1" colcount="1">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="T_Menu">Auto-Layer<text styleclass="Body Text HowTo"> edits the </text><text styleclass="ParameterHeader">Extrusion-Offset</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo"> and </text><text styleclass="ParameterHeader">Part-Offset</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo"> parameters (in the </text><text styleclass="Element">Extrusion dialog</text><text styleclass="Body Text">) to move </text><text styleclass="Interface2" style="color:#ff0000;">all</text><text styleclass="Body Text">&#32;</text><text styleclass="Element-Header">Extrusions</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> in the active </text><text styleclass="Interface">Mechanism-Editor</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> along the</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo"> Z-axis. </text></para>
          <para styleclass="VariableName"><text style="color:#ff0000;">Warning</text>:<text styleclass="Body Text HowTo"> You cannot </text><text styleclass="Interface2" style="color:#ff0000;">undo</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo"> the </text><text styleclass="T_Menu">Auto-Layer</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> command. </text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text">After you do <text styleclass="T_Menu">Auto-Layer</text>, <text styleclass="Element">Extrusions</text> should not collide with each other when you cycle the model. </para>
          <para styleclass="T_Menu">Auto-Layer<text styleclass="Body Text HowTo"> should save you time. However, </text>Auto-Layer<text styleclass="Body Text HowTo"> is not perfect!</text></para>
          <para styleclass="VariableName"><text styleclass="Body Text">If, after you use </text><text styleclass="T_Menu">Auto-Layer</text><text styleclass="Body Text">, the Extrusions collide, you need to each </text><text styleclass="Element">Extrusion</text><text styleclass="Body Text">. </text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#343400;" /></para>
    <para styleclass="SeeAlso">See also: <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Command-Solids-AutoProfiles">Auto-Profiles (Mechanism)</link>,<text styleclass="Body Text">&#32;</text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Command-Solids-AutoProfile">Auto-Profile (Part)</link>, Profile, <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Dialog-ProfileExtrusion">Extrusion dialog</link></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#343400;" /></para>
    <para styleclass="Notes">Top-Tip: </para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="1" colcount="1">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Body Text">Before you do <text styleclass="T_Menu">Auto-Layer</text>, you usually add <text styleclass="Element">Auto-Profiles</text> and/or <text styleclass="Element">Profiles</text> in the <text styleclass="Interface">Mechanism-Editor.</text></para>
          <list id="0" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="&#183;" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; color:#003300;">
            <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted">Do <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Command-Solids-AutoProfiles" styleclass="T_Menu">MD-Solids menu &gt; Auto-Profile (all Parts)</link></li>
            <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted"><text styleclass="T_Menu">Do </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Command-Solids-AutoProfile" styleclass="T_Menu">MD-Solids menu &gt; Auto-Profile (Part)</link></li>
            <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted">Do <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Command-Solids-Add-Profile" styleclass="T_Menu">MD-Solids menu &gt; Profile</link></li>
          </list>
          <para styleclass="Body Text">To see the <text styleclass="Interface2">MD</text><text styleclass="Interface">-SolidsL</text></para>
          <list id="1" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="&#183;" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; color:#003300;">
            <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted">Enable<text styleclass="Body Text HowTo">&#32;</text><text styleclass="T_Menu">Visibility menu &gt; </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Visibility-SolidsInMechanisms" styleclass="T_Menu">Show Solids in Mechanisms</link></li>
          </list>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#343400;" /></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading3_atocs_">Auto-Layer</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="2" colcount="2">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:240px;">
          <para styleclass="Image Caption"><image src="MD-Auto-Layer-0.ipp" imagestyleclass="Default" scale="-99.90%" figurelistinclude="0"><title>Before &apos;Auto-Layer&apos;</title><caption><![CDATA[Before 'Auto-Layer']]></caption></image></para>
        </td>
        <td rowspan="2">
          <list id="2" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="&#83;&#84;&#69;&#80;&#32;&#37;&#48;&#58;&#115;&#58;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="HowTo STEP" style="font-family:&apos;Segoe UI Semibold&apos;; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="HowTo STEP"><text styleclass="VariableName">Do the Auto-Layer command.</text></li>
          </list>
          <para styleclass="Body Text"><table styleclass="Block" rowcount="1" colcount="2">
            <tr style="vertical-align:top">
              <td style="vertical-align:bottom; width:41px;">
                <para styleclass="Image Caption"><image src="MD-Icon-AutoLayer.png" scale="100.00%" figurelistinclude="0"></image></para>
              </td>
              <td>
                <list id="3" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="&#37;&#48;&#58;&#115;&#46;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="B Bullets" style="font-family:&apos;Segoe UI Semibold&apos;; font-size:11pt; color:#003300;">
                  <li styleclass="B Bullets"><text styleclass="Body Text">Click </text><text styleclass="T_Menu">MD-Solids menu &gt; Auto-Layer</text></li>
                </list>
                <para styleclass="Body Text"><text style="font-family:&apos;Segoe UI Semibold&apos;; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; font-style:normal; text-transform:none; vertical-align:baseline; color:#000000; background-color:transparent; letter-spacing:normal; letter-scaling:100%;">OR</text></para>
                <list id="4" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="&#37;&#48;&#58;&#115;&#46;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="T_Menu" style="font-family:&apos;Segoe UI Semibold&apos;; font-size:11pt; color:#003300;">
                  <li styleclass="T_Menu"><text styleclass="Body Text">Click </text>MD-Solids toolbar &gt; Auto-Layer</li>
                </list>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </table></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text">The <text styleclass="T_Menu">Auto-Layer</text> command uses the <text styleclass="ParameterHeader">Extrusion-Offset</text> and <text styleclass="ParameterHeader">Part-Offset</text> parameters in <text styleclass="VariableName">Application-Settings &gt; Auto-Profile tab</text><text styleclass="Interface">&#32;</text>to calculate the offset of all <text styleclass="Element-Header">Extrusions</text> in the <text styleclass="Interface">Mechanism-Editor</text>.</para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text"></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:240px;">
          <para styleclass="Image Caption"><image src="MD-Auto-Layer-1.ipp" imagestyleclass="Default" scale="-99.90%" figurelistinclude="0"><title>After &apos;Auto-Layer&apos;</title><caption><![CDATA[After 'Auto-Layer']]></caption></image></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
